    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation
        - Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.4.4" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Valves</title>
        <figure id="f3450010070" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08133.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve seal assembly (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Valve seal assembly will not seat completely over valve guide by hand. Seals can be seated using a
                    deep socket and a rubber mallet to provide a positive contact with the machined base.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate inside of new valve seal assembly with clean engine oil and install on valve
                guide.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate valve stem with clean engine oil and insert valve in cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve spring over valve seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install valve spring retainer on top of valve spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010071" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve spring compression (typical)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve stem key (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">C Type Valve Spring Compressor ZTSE1846</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve spring retainer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure when the valve spring compressor is released the inside bead
                    of each key locks into the key groove of the valve stem.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress valve spring with
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_237.xml" xrefid="s10.t3">C Type Valve Spring Compressor ZTSE1846</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t3"/>, install two valve stem keys, and release spring compressor.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After valve replacement, measure valve head recession relative to deck to confirm
                reconditioning. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
